data.title: Most Frequent Word
data.statement: You are given a list of words. Your task is to determine the word that appears the most number of times. If multiple words have the same highest frequency, print the one that appears first among them in the input.

lastVersion.statementHTML:
Goal

You are given a list of words. Your task is to determine the word that appears the most number of times. If multiple words have the same highest frequency, print the one that appears first among them in the input.
Input
Line 1: An integer n — the number of words.
Next n Lines: each line contains a single word.
Output
Line 1: A single word — the one that occurred most frequently. If there's a tie, return the one that appeared first.
Constraints
1 ≤ n ≤ 500
Each word is a lowercase string of up to 20 letters.
Example
Input
5
apple
banana
banana
apple
orange
Output
apple
